args: So you're sayin' that other than your\nown and Mym's names, yer mind's a\nblank slate?
That seems to be the case... I'm sorry.
Perhaps this is his body's stress response\nto the trauma he just experienced.
The fact that he only remembers Mym\ncould be because he was trying to help\nher just before he went under.
Uh, so what do we do about this, then?\nAre his memories gone for good?
I have an idea! There's a place pretty close\nto this beach where medicinal herbs grow.\nMaybe we'll find something helpful there.
Good thinking, Luca. I'll go with you to\ninvestigate.
I'll go check with the nearby church\nand see if they're aware of any\ntreatments for memory loss.
I'll assist with that. If we're gathering\ninfo, many hands make for lighter work.
Truth. I'll go see what info I can dig up\nin the port town.
Mym, you stay with the prince. I think it'd\nbe better if the both of you kept resting.
Plus, I think he'll feel better if he's with\nsomeone he actually remembers. We're\ncountin' on you.
I'm sorry everyone has to go to all this\ntrouble on my account.
Don't you waste another second worrying\nabout that! The only thing you need to be\ndoing is taking it easy.
(He looks so uneasy. Not that I blame him,\nwhat with his memories lost and all.)
(So long as he's incapacitated on my\naccount, it's my responsibility to get\nhim back into ship-shape!)
(But...how? What can I do\nto make him smile again?)
(Ugh, how embarrassing.\nAlthough now that I think about it...!)
You can't expect to get your memories\nback without some fuel in the tank, silly.
You make a valid point. Time to eat, then.
Hee hee. There's that smile I love.

I always see you beaming when you're
eating with everyone, so I figured a good
meal might put a little of the old pep
back into your step.
This is so nice. Thank you, Mym.\nSay... Would you tell me about myself?
I'd like to know more about what kind of\nperson I am.
Of course. Let's see... I'll start by talking\nabout the time when I met you.
...That about sums it up. You were\nso cool back then, it made my heart\npositively throb!
I see. It's...kind of hard to believe.
Because you're talking about me like I'm\nthis reliable, charismatic person.
Well, it's all true. Not one word of what\nI say is an exaggeration.
You're going to make me blush. But...
Even after listening to you, I still don't\nremember anything. I can't imagine I'm\nworth all your praise like this.
Sorry. You went out of your way to tell\nme all of this, and now it sounds like\nI'm trying to shut you down.
Like I told you, you've been a fighter all\nalong. You've never given up.
And in the past, you've needed time off.\nJust think of this incident as a little\nsummer vacation from your burdens.
You always put others first. So today,\nI only want you to think about you.
Relax! We're all here with you!
I promise you that we're going to get\nyour memories back.
I... Thank you. I'm really glad you're here.
(No, no, no... Come on, Mym! The poor boy\nis in a bona fide crisis. This is no time to\ngo all weak in the knees.)
Hey, here's an idea: now that you're\nfull, how about a walk on the beach?
Your memories might come back easier\nthan we expect if you relax a bit.
(Gah. Bad Mym! I refuse to be the kind of\nwoman who lets her feelings run amok at\na time like this!)
